This paper is about developing a large-scale fraud detection system for e-commerce insurance, which involves processing big graphs containing millions of nodes and billions of edges. The paper discusses the use of different graphs to facilitate fraudster mining and the application of supervised and unsupervised graph learning algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.DB (Databases), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
